I had shared my code to you.

there are two folders in the custom_lib_error.tar.gz: custom_Layer and mnist_repo; custom_layer is the custom of  operator, custom_layer/build/libextension. so is the use of the operator avx512 library, custom_layer /no_avx512/ libextension.so is a shared library compiled without avX512. It is compiled in openvino centos7 2021.3 runtime image.

how to get libextension.so:
```shell
cd custom_Layer 
cd build && cmake ..
make
```

repeat the steps in Model Server2021.3:

> with avx512:

```shell
./ovms --model_path /data/mnist_repo/mnist --model_name mnist --port 9000 --cpu_extension /data/custom_layer/build/libextension.so --plugin_config '{"CPU_THROUGHPUT_STREAMS": "12"}' --shape auto

There is probably something missing in package with instructions we received since I was unable to build library straight away:
```

Could you try switching gcc version?

@atobiszei sorry, the information was a little confusing, so let me rearrange it.
because the centos image version of GCC is 4.x, but 4.x does not support avx512 instruction, so I upgraded the GCC version to 8.x, so that the normal compilation can be done.

there is no farmhash library in the system, you can install it.

you can download farmhash rpm with this link:
[https://distrib-coffee.ipsl.jussieu.fr/pub/linux/altlinux/p10/branch/x86_64/RPMS.classic/farmhash-1.1-alt2.x86_64.rpm](https://distrib-coffee.ipsl.jussieu.fr/pub/linux/altlinux/p10/branch/x86_64/RPMS.classic/farmhash-1.1-alt2.x86_64.rpm)

Then there is issue with missing `libonnx_importer.so`. Do you have Dockerfile based on OVMS Dockerfile to share?

Please try building no_avx version of library with updated gcc (the same you used to compile one with AVX512). I suspect this is the issue.
libonnx_importer.so is located in the OVMS 2021.3 image /ovms/lib/libonnx_importer.so,  you can check whether there is libonnx_importer.so, this shared library is existing with OVMS image.
